# Payment Pages (SwiftPay Builder)

Module: `/payment-pages` and create-page wizard. Defines page shell, steps, and builder layout (not individual UI components).

## Dashboard (`/payment-pages`)
- Standard page pattern: `px-[32px] pt-[12px] pb-[32px] bg-white min-h-full`
- Action bar: "Create Page" Primary CTA (High emphasis, `Plus` icon) + search + filters
- Table: `grid-cols-[1.5fr_1.5fr_1fr_0.8fr_0.8fr_0.4fr]`, without vertical separators
- Status chips: Active `text-[#21c179] bg-[#e3f6ec]`, Expired `text-[#fd5154] bg-[#ffebef]`, Draft `text-[#7e7e7e] bg-[#fafafa]`
- Actions: kebab menu (Share, Download QR, Edit, Expire/Reactivate, Delete)

## Create Page Entry
- Popup (`type="form"`) with 4 option cards
- Each card: `border border-[#e0e0e0] rounded-[12px] p-5 hover:bg-[#f5f9fe]`
- Icon: `size-10 rounded-[8px] bg-[#e0f5fd]`

## Step Wizard
- Component spec and tokens: **`.cursor/rules/components/step-wizard.mdc`**
- Used on all three wizard screens: `PageInfoForm`, `PageBuilder`, `AdditionalSettings`

## Wizard footer (`PageLevelMenu`)
- Shared sticky footer on **Step 1 & 3** ‚ÄĒ see **`.cursor/rules/components/page-level-menu.mdc`**
- Step 2 (Page Builder) uses **BuilderTopBar** instead

## Step 1: Page Information (`PageInfoForm.tsx`)
- **Spacing:** No extra top padding on the main content wrapper (`pt-0`); vertical gap after the step card comes from `StepWizard`'s nav `pb-5` only. Content **left-aligned** in the frame (`justify-start`, same `px-[32px]` as the wizard)
- **No card** around fields: **two-column grid** is `w-full` edge-to-edge within horizontal padding (`grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2`, **`gap-x-6`** = **24px** horizontal gap between columns, `gap-y-5` vertical)
- **6 fields** in 3 rows (2 per row):
  - Row 1: **Payment Page Name** (text, required) | **Payment Page Category** (select dropdown, required ‚ÄĒ Education, Donations, Events, eCommerce, Services, Subscriptions, Other)
  - Row 2: **Business Email** (email, required) | **Business Phone Number** (text, required)
  - Row 3: **Payment Page Expiry Date** (date, optional) | **Browser Tab Display Name** (text, required)
- Category field uses a custom `CategorySelect` with floating-label style matching `TextField` (`h-[56px]`, `rounded-[4px]`, same border/hover colors)
- Header: title + single subtitle line (`text-[#7e7e7e]`)
- All text inputs use `TextField` (floating-label, 56px, `rounded-[4px]`); wrap each field in `min-w-0` for grid overflow
- Actions: **`PageLevelMenu`** ‚ÄĒ Cancel + Continue to Page Builder (`primaryDisabled` until all required fields filled); no Clear all

## Step 2: Page Builder ‚ÄĒ Structured Payment Page Builder

### Architecture
This is a **structured payment page builder**, NOT a freeform form builder. The artboard has **4 fixed, non-deletable sections** in a strict order:
1. **Branding** ‚ÄĒ logo, business name, cover image, description, video
2. **Product / Items** ‚ÄĒ single/multiple/catalog modes, item cards, pricing
3. **Customer Details** ‚ÄĒ name, contact, optional fields in 2-column grid
4. **CTA** ‚ÄĒ sticky payment button, amount summary, configurable label

### Types (`builder-types.ts`)
- `SectionId`: `"branding" | "product" | "customer" | "cta"`
- `SECTION_ORDER`: fixed array governing section order
- `StructuredPageState`: full page state containing `BrandingData`, `ProductData`, `CustomerData`, `CTAData`, `PageCustomization`
- `isSectionComplete()` / `isPageValid()`: validation helpers

### Layout: StepWizard + Builder Workspace
1. **StepWizard** (Frame 1): identical to Steps 1 & 3
2. **Builder Workspace** (Frame 2): `BuilderTopBar` + three-panel layout on dotted canvas

### Top bar (`BuilderTopBar.tsx`, `h-[56px]`)
- Left: editable page title (click to rename, inline input)
- Center: Desktop/Mobile toggle + Fit to screen
- Right: Preview, Save Draft, Continue (disabled until `isPageValid()`)

### Three-panel layout

- **Left ‚ÄĒ Section Component Library** (`SectionComponentLibrary.tsx`, `w-[260px]`):
  - Section-aware: filters components by selected section
  - Search across all components
  - Section tabs: All | Branding | Products | Customer | CTA
  - Click-to-add (not drag-and-drop); components are added to the relevant section data

- **Center ‚ÄĒ Canvas Workspace** (`BuilderCanvas.tsx`, `flex-1`):
  - **Dotted grid background**: `radial-gradient(circle, #d4d4d4 1px, transparent 1px)`, scales with zoom
  - **Pan**: middle-click or Alt+drag
  - **Zoom**: Ctrl/‚Ćė + scroll / trackpad pinch, 40%-200%; floating zoom controls (‚ąí, %, +, Fit)
  - **Artboard** (`BuilderArtboard.tsx`): centered, responsive width (`max-w-[520px]` desktop, `max-w-[390px]` mobile)
    - Browser chrome bar at top (macOS-style traffic lights)
    - 4 sections rendered in fixed order
    - Click section to select ‚Üí highlights with `border-[#004299]` + shadow ring
    - Section label badge appears on hover/selection

- **Right ‚ÄĒ Property Panel** (`PropertyPanel.tsx`, `w-[300px]`):
  - Two tabs: **Section Properties** | **Customize**
  - **Section Properties**: contextual editor for the selected section
    - Branding: logo upload, business name, cover image, description, video URL
    - Product: mode selector (single/multiple/catalog), pricing type, item list (expand/collapse per item), donation goal (collapsible)
    - Customer: field list with inline editing (label, placeholder, type, required, width), add/remove fields
    - CTA: label selector (Pay Now/Donate Now/Subscribe/Enrol Now/Submit/custom), amount summary toggle
  - **Customize**: theme panel ‚ÄĒ primary/secondary/background colors (native color picker), font family, 1-column/2-column layout toggle
  - **Empty state**: "Select a section on the artboard‚Ä¶"

### Section Components

- **BrandingSection** (`BrandingSection.tsx`): cover image with logo overlay, business name, description, video placeholder; uses `PageCustomization` colors/fonts
- **ProductSection** (`ProductSection.tsx`): mode badge, item cards (inline ‚Č§3, "View all" if >3), donation goal progress bar, auto-calculated total
- **CustomerDetailsSection** (`CustomerDetailsSection.tsx`): field previews in 2-col grid (desktop) or 1-col (mobile), "Add field" hint
- **CTASection** (`CTASection.tsx`): amount summary bar, full-width CTA button styled with primary color, trust badges

### Guided Overlay (`GuidedOverlay.tsx`)
- Shown on first load (`showGuide` state)
- Modal with gradient header (progress bar), 4 step cards
- Each step shows: completion indicator, label, guide copy
- Current incomplete section highlighted with ring
- "Get Started" / "Continue Building" / "Done ‚ÄĒ Continue" button
- Dismissable (X or action button)

### Validation & Continue
- `isPageValid()`: checks all 4 sections meet minimum requirements
- Branding: business name required
- Product: at least 1 item with title and price > 0
- Customer: at least 1 required field
- CTA: label must not be empty
- Continue button disabled until valid; autosave debounced (2s)

## Step 3: Additional Settings
- Primary tabs: Post Transaction | Notifications
- Post Transaction: Redirect URL, Success Message
- Notifications: SMS toggle + text, Email toggle + subject + body
- **Footer**: `PageLevelMenu` with `primaryEmphasis="success"` ‚ÄĒ Back to Builder + Save & Publish (`bg-[#21c179]`); no Clear all
